Saga</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usiffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silly old Rogue</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 10:57:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues tanking (to Siffo)</span><hr size=1> Thanks Captain Tita, you did it very nicley.<br>
<br>
As she said these are lower level mobs, many of them I could probably solo my self. I have to be able to absorb a lot of punishment but still use evade and backstab.<br>
<br>
My choices are.<br>
<br>
Use my equipment as is. In which case after asecond into the battle the only way to try and loose aggro so I can BS is to evade and move out of range of the mob and even then they often turn right back to me when I get close.<br>
<br>
I could remove my SCHW and bump my AC with better gauntlets this would lower my aggro a bit and give me a slight increase in AC (about 5points I think) but my BS will also be much slower loosing a lot of DPS.<br>
<br>
Or I could carry a really good shield lossing my off hand weapon (Including BS in the equation lets say I loose 25% of my DPS output at most) I am still hasted so my BS is fast, I raise my AC significantly(AC 25 for the shield in question that is better than my best piece of armor) I have lowered my aggro some so hopefully I can evade and use my BS each time for high damage strike (BS is around 50% of my damge out put or more I think) .<br>
<br>
All and all it looks like the shield would be the way to go for these lower level groups where I am tanking. I don't know this for a fact and I haven't met any one who has tried it so there is no impirical evidence. I guess I will just have to try it and find out. Like I said in that other post the Bladestopper shield would have been a good test for this experiment. OH well I will try it.<br>
 <p>Siffo Corpsestalker<BR>
Death Night Rogue Warrior<BR>
47th Blade of Training<BR>
Unofficial Official Dues Collector<BR>

<img src="http://itsinhere.com/saga/Siffosig.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthevolcanogod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 12:42:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues tanking (to Siffo)</span><hr size=1> Hmm, not sure what your equipment is but if you have a halfway decent piercer in your mainhand, with haste you will still get Aggro 80-90% of the time (not sure what a SCHW is - it's a new term since I've been back from a year-long break from the game). I guess it would also depent on the makeup of your group. If you have a nuke heavy group where things die fast but you have occasional med breaks, you only will be tanking the mob briefly so your DPS makes less of a difference. In that case I would think a shield would be more of a help. If the fights last longer - maybe you are letting DOTs work or there are some secondary melees fighting like lower level Rangers or Shamans I think the offhand weapon would be better because it would mitigate damage by ending combat sooner.<br>
If you have decent equipment at your level, you will actually have a hard time avoiding aggro even with a warrior in your party. At 50 I was using a Trak Tooth in mainhand and a Locustlure in offhand with a FBSS. In Karnor's, unless the WAR had some low delay weapons and taunted constantly, Drolvargs would eventually turn to me and I would have to trust in evade. With a group of lower level melee, you might be able to time an evade/backstab combo just right. But you would have to be quick with the backstab because even if evade worked, it would turn back to you after your next hit or 2. So basically, I'm not sure - it would be more based on the particular situation and group makeup. The one thing I do know is that after 40, I hated being hit as a Rogue, then after 45 it started to become a problem if I attracted aggro, at my low 50s it often became deadly if I couldn't get rid of it and in mid 50's raids I would die if I attracted aggro for more than a couple seconds.<br>
Vulrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubippinfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bippinfv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf-hugger</span><br>  Posts: 799<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 12:57:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues tanking (to Siffo)</span><hr size=1> Another 2 cents to the pot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
SCHW is silver chitin hand wraps - haste gloves from Velks, 22% haste, 10AC , some stats and save. Siffo, you can try and get Rohal's gaunts instead, 25AC, to gain 15AC and lose the haste, but I hate to lose haste <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I'd rather haste and evade, and if needed turn attack off to control the aggro the way you want it.<br>
<br>
Vulrath, you were using two very high speed weapons, a slow proc, and a haste belt - I'm not surprised you were pulling aggro. Putting a nice slow non proccing weapon in off hand, with a good ratio, will get you more damage and less aggro. <br>
<br>
Siffo, backstab is nowhere near 50% of your damage output. Not until after 55 when you get double backstab. At your levels, from my parsing, you are at about 25-33% from backstab, depending on how much you get to see the back. When you tank, it's a lot less than that. 25AC, even if it's better than any single piece you have, is not that much. What's your AC now ? 700+ ? it's not a huge difference, really. And you'll be losing a lot of damage potential. That is probably why no-one tries it any more - I'm sure  that at one time someone did <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Bippin Tenderfoot <BR>
&lt;Saga&gt; <BR>
Caillou's Intended</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umithlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mithlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 8:28:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues tanking (to Siffo)</span><hr size=1> Having fought by Siffo's side, he takes aggro a LOT.  Even when the MT is closer to his level.  I think the idea of putting a shield in the offhand is to purposely reduce DPS so he can do an evade, get a backstab in, and get aggro back when tanking.  That way he still gets the main hand DPS and the backstab DPS, just losing offhand DPS.  Right now by not being able to shrug off aggro long enough to BS, he is losing BS DPS while keeping offhand DPS. <p>Mithlin Lussarrna<BR>
Rogue of 37 seasons<BR>
Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1454<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 9:15:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> A few things.<br>
<br>
One, rogues can tank at high level, in exp groups.  I do it plenty in velks and sebilis.  We need good gear for it, but if we have the gear, we dish out better taunt than warriors.  That said, a shield is brutal to our damage output.  Assuming roughly equivilent on and offhand weapons, a rogue does about 30% of their damage offhand, when backstab is not available.  Also, if you evade off the agro, lacking an offhander will make it hard to get it back.<br>
<br>
So lose the shield, you don't want it.  Assuming 20% of your damage output is backstab (pre 55 and without a high damage mainhander that's quite likely) and 30% of the remaining 80 is offhand, you lose nearly 50% of your damage output by tanking with a shield.  Remember, you can't bash.  BAD IDEA.  <br>
<br>
If you want to tank, here's how to do it.<br>
<br>
Get fast weapons.  Traks tooth comes to mind.  That will raise your mainhand damage output when not backstabbing.  Locusluster and Shadowrager are amazing tank weapons for rogues.  Cresent Blades of Luclin too.  That will keep taunt firmly on you and allow you to do respectable damage, on par with warriors. (ew)<br>
<br>
Now for your armour.  Keep the haste, you want that.  But there's some nice tank gear available for rogues.  Ravenscale Belt has 9 ac 25 hp and 5 sta, making it nice for the purpose.  Axgoreth's Belt of defense is wonderful too, and not too expensive.  Crystal Chitin gear is also high ac with some stats.  And get those hitponts up, you need all you can get.  Bracer of Fortitude and Bracer of Quickness will help you tank, though I prefer Might to Quickness.  If this gear sounds too expensive to you, well, just remember you're not built to tank, so you need good gear to do the job right.  Getting an 8th Coldain ring will also help.  If you need AC on your weapons try a Longsword of Ethereal Energy.  But for god's sake don't get a shield.<br>
<br>
With all this said, a rogue is not really a tank.  You have to be equiped like crazy to do it right.  If you can't find a tank to work with, try an enchanter, them chainstunning works fine.  Bards, necros, and shadowknights fearing also works.  Heck, you can try instill doubt a bit. <br>
<br>
But not a shield.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usiffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silly old Rogue</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/3/02 11:07:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> All very good answers and a lot to think about.<br>
<br>
