Siffo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1455<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/4/02 12:23:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> Siffo... if you can't lose agro you have a problem.  Your weapons are quite nice, but nothing completely absurd... so let's see what can be done.<br>
<br>
One, get a slower weapon offhand.  Centi Longsword, Longsword of Ethereal Energy, something slow.  You'll do the same damage but with less taunt.<br>
<br>
If your weapons are procing, that's a bad thing... procs make for extra taunt.<br>
<br>
Stay back, at the edge of melee range, and make sure your tank gets closer.  Proximity agro is your friend.<br>
<br>
Pickpocket (on failure), beg, instill doubt, and disarm all build taunt, so be careful there.<br>
<br>
Evade evade evade.  <br>
<br>
That's pretty much all I can say, the rest is experience.  But you should be able to hold your agro just under that of the main tank, so you can take it when needed from the cleric/enchanter/wizard/whatever.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usakharra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sakharra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/5/02 4:42:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> Rogues can tank to a degree at high levels even briefly on some raid MOBs with good healing but no where near as effectively as a tanking class and the group or raid is nearly always best off letting someone else hold agro so the rogue can deal damage.<br>
<br>
Also, some degree of tanking is necessary to keep your defensive skills up, you should try to cap them every level.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I agree, you realy should'nt be getting agro with a warrior in the group who is near your level, assuming the warrior is not the problem, lets look at causes.<br>
<br>
Is your hide skill maxxed for level ?  If not, fix that, its the single best thing you can do for evade.<br>
<br>
Are evades getting interrupted ?  Make sure you stand dead still and time the evade with the MOBs strikes, sometimes you have to be patient and take a little bit of a beating.  Also if you are using an evade macro with other skills in it, lose them.  Alot of rogues put several doability commands in an evade macro and each one adds just a little delay which can cause it to be interrupted.  <br>
<br>
Fight at maximum melee range and train your tanks to stand right in the monster's face, proximity helps agro on alot of monsters.  (Training groups to be rogue friendly is something you just have to get used to).<br>
<br>
Anyway, yes I do have a character on FV, yes I do try to roleplay when I can and enjoy it, so I feel like I can comment on this board =b<br>
