<br>
The problem is as Mith said I build up such a massive aggro load I can't throw it off properly a lot of times to get in a Backstab I often have to back way out of aggro range while in evade and still they often turn back to me when I get colse.<br>
<br>
What I am tring to do is keep my aggro border line so I can evade have the mob turn away I can backstab and regain aggro so the other lower members dont get mauled much.<br>
<br>
My idea was to increase my AC and loose a little DPS  whether or not it would work I have no idea. It seems that I can't explain very well because nobody seems to look at it the way I am describing it. <br>
<br>
I keep getting suggestions to get a tank : I can't or I would. <br>
<br>
That if I am tanking I should want aggro: I do but I want to loose it so I can baskstab which gets it right back but I can't loose it cause I get so much.<br>
<br>
I typicaly have some rogues and a ranger maybe a druid all usualy a fair number of levels lower than I am. What I need to do is be able to hold aggro and absorb damage but have my evades effective so I can get in backstabs.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1464<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/5/02 8:54:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> Siffo... on evasion success you are automatically put between the highest agro and second highest agro people other than yourself, so you can still evade and stab with or without your shield... but with the shield you will do far less damage, which is less helpful to you than the AC increase.  <br>
<br>
Believe me, I solo and tank at times.  You don't want a shield.  Maybe a high AC weapon, but not a sheild.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usakharra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sakharra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/7/02 2:19:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Sak... you sure about hide skill? As far as I know, evade succeeds 66% of the time, lowering 500 hate or putting you between the first and second people on the hate list (if you were on the top), no matter what the skill level of the rogue.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm reasonably sure that evade is based on the hide skill or that hide skill plays a role in successful evades  However I've been wrong in the past and &quot;reasonably sure&quot; is by no means certain that there is a direct tie.  Lets say I feel safe operating under the assumption but 66 percent sounds about right as well.  Although at times I'd debate that after failing 7 in a row and doing some involuntary tanking.  <br>
<br>
Rememeber at low levels it was possible to &quot;fail&quot; a hide and still see a scowls con even when hidden ?  I really do think evade does a skill check on the hide skill,  In part it comes down to thats what I was told when I was &quot;growing up&quot; and I've never seen anything either posted or in game to make me doubt it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm not going to claim to be &quot;all knowing&quot; because I certainly am not :-) <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11990"><img src ="http://acropolis2.premiumchat.com/Sakharra/Saksig2.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usakharra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sakharra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/7/02 2:30:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> Oh Siffo, I apologize and I did indeed misunderstand the question early on.<br>
<br>
Lowering your DPS will help fine tune agro but its always going to be a very careful balancing act.  You could even got to a slasher or basher mainhand and swap in a piercer to backstab but the DPS drop there may be so extreme you cant keep agro when you want it.  I'd do that before I went piercer and sheild however.  Small gains in AC wont help much because rogues just dont work like that, your always going to get hit relatively hard compared to a true tanking class.<br>
<br>
Also here is something that was HARD for me to understand until Gayana rammed it through my thick blue skull in alot of duos.  It may be best just to let whoever you are partnered with hold agro so long as its not a &quot;robe&quot; caster.  I always looked at the shaman as a healer who needed to med, but with her &quot;tanking&quot; for me we were far more efficient that we were with me tanking.  <br>
<br>
Do you hunt with anyone who can root ?  If so then root is perhaps the best agro control in the game as it mostly nullifies the hate list.   Under melee it will have to be recast alot but it may be the solution you need.<br>
 <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11990"><img src ="http://acropolis2.premiumchat.com/Sakharra/Saksig2.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugegblix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gegblix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/7/02 10:44:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> Do you group with anyone who can root?<br>
<br>
When most mobs are rooted, they work off proximity agro.  Basically they hit whoever is closest and still on their hate list.  Root the mob, step in very close when you want agro, step back far away when you don't.  Keep that mob perma rooted.  Just make sure your groupmates are doing the same thing...does no good for you to be bouncing back and forth if half your group is stepping right on the mob's toes the entire fight.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shabbashadowsong>Shabba Shadowsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/8/02 12:46:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2838.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanky rogues</span><hr size=1> Siffo, in refeference to your gear, I don't know what belt you are using but I play a Bard and I would not use SCHW if someone gave them to me.<br>
<br>
You say a 25AC shield is better than any piece you have?  You need to get forhals gauntlets, 25ac.  For haste, decent AC and good stats get the grimling skullcracker belt.  I think that combo is more effective.  You give up maybe 7 percent haste but you get alot more AC.  If you are taking alot of hits you want the best AC you can get.  It will help alot more than that 7 percent haste on just you.  Factor in the total amount of dmg from your whole group and you are giving up very little dmg output.  Getting better AC will make you avoid more hits and take less dmg overall.<br>
<br>
For the price you can get for your SCHW you can pick up the grimling belt and the forhals gauntlets and still have some coin left over for some food and drink.<br>
<br>
Then again as a bard haste equip does not mean nearly as much to me, I carry my main haste in my songs so YMMV.<br>
